Let us stress that the vacuum space  as a whole is Poincare invariant, whereas a concrete vector  is only covariant: The wave function transforms as a mass- scalar field which carries the unitary representation ; the exponent comes from the vacuum part of 4-momentum and can be removed by a unitary transformation. The vacuum space plays a role of a base space in a bundle whose fibers are Fock spaces generated in the usual way in terms of the representation of CAR. The structure of the fibers is characterized by a theorem on the thermodynamic limit  (the proof is exactly analogous to the bosonic case explained in detail in). 
